Degree and careers information comes from What Do Graduates Do?, produced by AGCAS and Prospects. All data is derived from the HESA Destination of Leavers of Higher

What kind of career could a science, technology,
engineering or maths (STEM) degree lead to?
You might be surprised to know that a degree in
biology might help you become a zookeeper, or
that mechanical engineering could land you a job
If you havent thought quite that far ahead, thats
OK. Take a look at all the different jobs and
went on to do and see which A-Levels you might
need. Then talk to your teachers about which
STEM degrees open the door to all sorts of
interesting and often lucrative careers, in a wide
variety of industries, some quite unexpected!
Whether you want to be a manager or a musician,
site engineer or soccer coach, researcher or radio
producer, a STEM degree can help get you there!
